<font color="#FF0000">DON'T BE SO QUICK TO JUDGE.</font><br>
<tt>Tue Nov 16 12:09:19 US/Eastern 1999
</tt><p>
DE'YONA MADE A MISTAKE, BUT WE ALL MAKE MISTAKES, ONE TIME OR ANOTHER; SO ALL OF YOU PEOPLE WHO ARE SO QUICK TO JUDGE, YOU NEED TO LOOK AT YOUR OWN LIFE AND THINK ABOUT ALL THE THINGS THAT YOU COULD HAVE OR SHOULD HAVE DONE BUT DIDN'T.  WHAT IF SOMEONE WAS QUICK TO JUDGE YOU AND YOUR ACTIONS.  I BET IT WOULDN'T MAKE YOU FEEL THE BEST.  <br><br>
I BECAME PREGNANT MY SOPHOMORE YEAR IN COLLEGE.  I'M IN COLLEGE AND I KNEW THE CONSEQUENCES OF MY ACTIONS, BUT IT HAPPENED, JUST LIKE IT HAPPENS TO SO MANY PEOPLE EVERYDAY.  THE VERY ONES WHO ARE CRITICAL AND SO JUDGEMENTAL WILL BE THE VERY ONES TO END UP PREGNANT. WHO ARE YOU TO TELL SOMEONE WHAT THEY SHOULD HAVE DONE WHEN MOST OF YOU DON'T ACT ON WHAT YOU PREACH.<br><br>
IT NEVER SEEMS TO AMAZE ME HOW PEOPLE COULD BE SO JUDGEMENTAL.  I MEAN, HAVE SOME SYMPATHY FOR THE POOR GIRL.  JUST THINK OF ALL THE THINGS THAT WERE GOING THROUGH HER HEAD AT THE TIME.  THIS WAS A PERSON WHO HAD ASPIRATIONS, BUT THEY WERE DISRUPTED BY AN AWEFUL TRAGEDY.  THINK OF HOW THE THINGS IN YOUR LIFE WOULD CHANGE IF YOU WERE TO LOSE A LOVED ONE. 
